On the other hand, some of the driving factors for the growth of the global automatic chemistry urine analyzer market are a rise in the prevalence of chronic diseases, advancements in technology, and increased healthcare expenditure. However, high cost-related challenges and regulatory hurdles may be impediments to growth. Despite these, the general outlook for this market segment is still very good. Continuous innovations, coupled with the upgradation of healthcare infrastructure in emerging markets, would further open prospects for this segment.


